content.description: Wandering up the center of the wall this route might get the award for sharpest route at the Fins.  Start with a surprisingly hard move off the flake to 3 bolts of easy and sharp climbing angling right.  The business starts as you make your way into the sloper and a very sharp pocket pinch.  One long move gains the last obvious hold until you reach the anchors.  Overall great climbing but docked a star due to the amount of cleaning I had to do up top, the sharpness down low and an anchor setup that isn't ideal.
content.protection: bolts to an offset anchor and single biner.

content.description: On the left side of the wall, this has one hard move to gain the pod and a rest, then continue up brown, sharp, and chossy stone to join the seam at the top.  Worth doing if you've done the other 11s in the area.

The namesake route for the wall, this is a bolted crack that trends right before heading straight up at the top.  It's possible to escape right into the chossy flakes down low but staying the line is just as easy.  Exit the crack up high to a cool undercling and a pod.
content.protection: 10 bolts and chains (there are no biners in these chains)
content.location: Rightmost route on this small wall.  Follows the obvious crack.
